RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 4 1M 70Y Turf CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 133 lbs.; Older, 136 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAPINSKI UNION raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path, kicked clear in the stretch and held that margin to the wire. MINTENON raced in the two path around the first turn, opened up on the field racing up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the second turn and kept on to the finish. GRUNION saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and chased the winner home in the lane. RULE BREAKER bumped with the horses to his outside at the start, raced in the four path around the first turn, chased the frontrunner up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the four path and finished evenly. I WANNA ROCK veered in sharply and bumped with the horses to his inside leaving the gate, raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, raced in tight quarters, bumping with SHIP MASTER approaching the far turn, navigated the far turn from the two path, raced into traffic with the loose horse and was forced to check in the final furlong and was outkicked from there. RUGBY ROAD raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and flattened out in the lane. LT'S JACKNTHEBOX saved ground around the first turn, checked and nearly lost his rider entering the backstretch, raced off the pace between horses from there, ran out coming off the far turn and never threatened, finishing with his rider standing in the irons. MY BIG DRAMA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, drifted out and bumped with SHIP MASTER coming off the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and faded in the stretch. SETTE STELLE was bumped hard at the start of the race, settled at the back of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn still in the two path and was empty in the lane. SHIP MASTER was bumped by the horses to both sides leaving the gate, angled in to save ground around the first turn, raced off the pace up the backstretch, bumped with both I WANNA ROCK and MY BIG DRAMA approaching the far turn, falling in the process and later walked off. INBOUND reared and veered out at the start, causing his rider to loose a iron in the process, raced in the four path around the first bend, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, lost his rider coming around the second bend, was pulled up after the wire and walked off. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THIS RACE. UPON REVIEW, HORSE ELEVEN, I WANNA ROCK, WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE WITH MULTIPLE HORSES. HORSE TWO, MY BIG DRAMA, WAS ALSO DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED SECOND TO LAST FOR INTERFERENCE ON THE BACKSTRETCH WITH HORSE NINE, SHIP MASTER.
